formattedAddress: 4 Union Square South (btwn Broadway & University Pl)

venue.header: According to the Foursquare community, this place is an 8.3 out of 10.
venue.explanation: We take into account visits and input from our community. You'll see a number on places based off of ratings and tips written by people like you.

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: Welcome to New York, NY Whole Foods Market! Whole Foods is the leading retailer of natural and organic foods uniquely positioned as America's Healthiest Grocery Store.

pageInfo.description: Whole Foods Market is the world's largest natural and organic grocer. Find one near you, check in, and say hello!

items.text: The long lines here will lead you to check in and leave tips on foursquare.
Great selection of organic products and great selection of sugar derivatives for people with diabetes. I did a dinner and made desserts using Stevia. -Ed Cotton, Top Chef
Pick up our Pepper Sauce, carrot juice, orange juice, ginger, lemon juice, parsley. Use those to make the March Hare, our fresh take on the classic Bloody Mary (vodka sold separately)

items.name: NYC: Gluten-Free Globetrotter
items.description: Gluten-free friendly in New York City. Blogging at Gluten-Free Fun and Gluten-Free Globetrotter. Tweeting at @gfreefun and @gfglobetrotter. Living with Celiac Disease since 1981

tip.text: Always crowded, but there is a huge selection of gluten-free food. Tip: Whole Foods accepts manufacturers coupons and also has their own coupons on their website. Clip, print, and save!
